00:32:19.540 --> 00:32:23.400
But these help commands are a special
type of URL you can use in your content.

00:32:23.400 --> 00:32:25.220
You notice they all
start with help colon,

00:32:25.220 --> 00:32:28.760
which is a special handler we've
defined for the help viewer.

00:32:28.900 --> 00:32:30.990
And by using these commands,
you can cause the help

00:32:31.010 --> 00:32:31.970
viewer to do things.

00:32:32.140 --> 00:32:34.570
You can tell it to go to the help center.

00:32:34.670 --> 00:32:35.990
You can switch to another book.

00:32:36.090 --> 00:32:38.750
For example,
if you want to take somebody to Mac Help,

00:32:38.750 --> 00:32:42.700
you can include a link in your content
that says open Mac Help for me.

00:32:42.860 --> 00:32:46.700
When they click that,
the help viewer will go find Mac Help.

00:32:46.700 --> 00:32:48.390
You can open to an anchor in a book.

00:32:48.390 --> 00:32:51.120
So if you want to refer to a
specific page either within

00:32:51.120 --> 00:32:54.690
your own book or someone else's,
you can refer to it by anchor

00:32:54.690 --> 00:32:57.900
without having to know its file
name or location on the disk.

00:33:00.750 --> 00:33:01.450
A couple more.

00:33:01.450 --> 00:33:02.980
You can perform a search.

00:33:02.990 --> 00:33:04.520
You saw this in the demo.

00:33:04.590 --> 00:33:07.300
Tell me more,
our quick clicks that were in the demo.

00:33:07.300 --> 00:33:09.700
Those all perform a search
within the help viewer.

00:33:09.700 --> 00:33:13.370
